CustomFunction.Calculation:
// ValueOrDefault ( SomeValue; DefaultValue )
// version 1.0, Erik Shagdar, NYHTC


/*
	Takes 2 values, uses the first one if the first is NOT empty, uses the second ( default ) if first is empty


NOTE:
	the test is only for a NULL value, if 'SomeValue' evaluates to 'False' ( 0, false, etc... ) it would still be used.


HISTORY:
	1.0 - 2015-11-11 ( eshagdar ): created
*/



If ( not IsEmpty ( SomeValue );
	SomeValue;
	DefaultValue
)
